---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import CardGrid from "../../components/CardGrid.astro";
import Card from "../../components/Card.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="Getting Started" section="getting_started">
  <h1>Getting started with Pixano</h1>
  <p>
    Pixano is an open-source data-centric AI tool for exploring and annotating computer vision datasets.
    It combines a Python/FastAPI backend with a Svelte/TypeScript frontend and stores data in the fast,
    columnar Lance format.
  </p>

  <CardGrid>
    <Card title="Installation" href="/getting_started/installing_pixano/" icon="download">
      All the ways to install Pixano: pip, Docker, or from source.
    </Card>
    <Card title="Quickstart" href="/getting_started/quickstart/" icon="rocket">
      Import a dataset with pre-annotations and launch the app in minutes.
    </Card>
    <Card title="Key Concepts" href="/getting_started/key_concepts/" icon="lightbulb">
      Understand the data model: items, views, entities, annotations, and more.
    </Card>
  </CardGrid>

  <p>
    Once you are comfortable with the basics, head over to the
    <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}use_cases/`}>Use Cases</a> for end-to-end walkthroughs with real datasets.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
